article.headline: North Dakota 83, Houston Baptist 73
article.story: GRAND FORKS, N.D. -- Aaron Anderson scored 16 points to lead five North Dakota players in double figures as part of an 83-73 victory over Houston Baptist on Saturday. Trailing by three points in the second half, the Fighting Sioux (10-10, 3-1 Great West) went on a 17-4 run in the final six minutes for the win. Brandon Brekke and Josh Schuler added 15 points each for North Dakota while Patrick Mitchell scored 11 and Chris Clausen 10. The Huskies (2-18, 1-4) led by as many as eight points in the first half but went into halftime trailing 41-36. Andrew Gonzalez led Houston Baptist with a game-high 23 points while Terry Bembry added 16 and Michael Moss 11. The Huskies grabbed the rebounding advantage 33-30.
